The paper discusses the use of antenna arrays and beamforming techniques in 5G systems, which are typically studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and communications (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of millimeter wave spectrum and analog front-end design also relates to the field of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different beamforming techniques in the presence of quantization noise, which is a topic studied in the field of computer architecture (cs.AR).
